and":"Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Longnor, Shropshire, England":"Longnor, Shropshire, England"},"en":{"1467–1485":"1467–1485","1463–1538":"1463–1538","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","1420":"1420","1485":"1485","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","Abt. 1485":"about 1485","1470":"1470","about 1484":"about 1484","1538":"1538","Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England":"Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England","Bestowe, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Beslow, Shropshire, England.":"Shropshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","Longnor, Shropshire, England":"Longnor, Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Eaton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Eaton or Eton, such as Eaton Socon (Bedfordshire), Eaton (Cheshire), or Eton (Buckinghamshire), named from either Old English <i>ēa</i> ‘river’ or <i>ēg</i> ‘island, low-lying land’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’.","History: Nathaneal Eaton, born in Coventry, England, <i>c.</i> 1609, came to MA in 1637 and was the first head of Harvard College, in 1638–39."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lucia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of the old Roman given name <i>Lucius</i>, which is probably a derivative of Latin <i>lux</i> ‘light’. The girl's name is common in Italy and elsewhere, and is found as a learned, Latinate doublet of   Lucy   in England.  St Lucia  of Syracuse, who was martyred in  304 , was a very popular saint in the Middle Ages; she is often represented in medieval art as blinded and with her eyes on a platter, but the tradition that she had her eyes put out is probably based on nothing more than the association between light and eyes."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lucia Eaton was born in 1467, in Longnor, Shropshire, England, her father, Hezekiah Eyton, was 47 and her mother, Elizabeth Thomas, was 17. She married Sir Thomas Poyner about 1484, in Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1485, in her hometown, at the age of 18."},"et":{"1467–1485":"1467–1485","1463–1538":"1463–1538","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","1420":"1420","1485":"1485","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","Abt. 1485":"umbes 1485","1470":"1470","about 1484":"umbes 1484","1538":"1538","Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England":"Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England","Bestowe, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Beslow, Shropshire, England.":"Shropshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Longnor, Shropshire, England":"Longnor, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1467–1485":"1467–1485","1463–1538":"1463–1538","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","1420":"1420","1485":"1485","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","Abt. 1485":"noin 1485","1470":"1470","about 1484":"noin 1484","1538":"1538","Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England":"Eyton near Wem, Shropshire, England","Bestowe, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Beslow, Shropshire, England.":"Shropshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Longnor, Shropshire, England":"Longnor, Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"1467–1485":"1467–1485","1463–1538":"1463–1538","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","1420":"1420","1485":"